net.openhft.chronicle.decentred.util

Interface DtoRegistry<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the super interface for all dto:s
    All Superinterfaces:
    HasSuperInterface<T>, Supplier<DtoParser<T>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    VanillaDtoRegistry

    public interface DtoRegistry<T>
extends Supplier<DtoParser<T>>, HasSuperInterface<T>
    A holder of the different protocols that are available for all data transfer objects (dto:s) and can supply new DtoParser objects.

      • addProtocol

        DtoRegistry<T> addProtocol(int protocol,
                           Class<? super T> pClass)
        Adds a new protocol for this registry with the provided protocol number protocol and provided protocol class pClass.

        The given protocol will be associated with the given pClass.

        The provided pClass objects must contain at least one method annotated with the MethodId annotation or this method will have no effect.

        Parameters:
        protocol - number to use
        pClass - protocol class to be associated
        Returns:
        this (potentially modified) DtoRegistry
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided protocol is negative or if the protocol otherwise cannot be added to this registry.
        NullPointerException - if the provided pClass is null
